page.title: 19COUNTRYSIDE IN DALWOOD.
page.content: In Dalwood there are a lot of rabbits and some foxes, but not many.There are badgers as well.There are quite a lot of squirrels. Sometimes they get run over. There are one or two herons. There are weasels and stoats which eat things like rabbits and hares.There are rats and mice in hay stacks.There are pheasants with their chicks in the fields.They sit on the ground and they use that place as a nest.Bats can be found in any old house pub or cottage in the attic . There are adders,slow worms and grass snakes.Grass snakes and adders are found in hedges and slow worms are found under pieces of wood. Cattle, pigs and poultry are kept on the farms.
